The paper deals with a specific class of logic programs, namely dual-normal programs, and studies their properties and relationships with other classes of programs. This falls under the area of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as logic programming is a popular tool in AI. The paper also involves logical reasoning and complexity analysis, which are topics in Logic (cs.LO) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper introduces a new class of programs, body-cycle free programs, which could be of interest to researchers in Data Structures (cs.DS) and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
